      {q:"What does the 'I' in ACID stand for and mean?",opts:["A. Isolation: Concurrent transactions execute without interfering with each other (e.g., they don't see each other's uncommitted data).","B. Internet: Requires a web connection","C. Integration: Works with other databases","D. Iteration: Loops through data"],ans:0,exp:"Isolation prevents 'Dirty Reads' and race conditions when thousands of users access the database at once."},
