      {q:"What does 'Consistency' ensure in an ACID database?",opts:["A. The database is consistently fast","B. Any transaction will bring the database from one valid state to another valid state, strictly adhering to all defined rules, constraints, and cascades","C. The code looks consistent","D. Backups are consistent"],ans:1,exp:"If a transaction tries to insert a String into an Integer column, it violates consistency and will be rejected."},
